    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>July 19. 1856</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend—</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Enclosed<lb/> please find duplicate of draft for<lb/> $50 original
                of which I have<lb/> sent by mail, &amp; which I hope, has<lb/> duly come to
                hand.</p>
            <p>I have seen <persName>Mr. L. L. Dennery</persName>, who<lb/> has told me, that he has
                paid your<lb/> agent, <persName>Mr Isaac Hart</persName>, at <placeName>New
                    Or-<lb/>-leans</placeName> up to the year <date>'52</date>, &amp; that<lb/> was
                all he owed you for, as in<lb/> that year he had left <placeName>N. O.</placeName>,
                &amp; that<lb/> he had then given you due notice of<lb/> his desire of discontinuing
                the Occid.<lb/> “The Ladies United Hebrew Benevolent<lb/> Society” held their
                semi-yearly<lb/> meeting on the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of February</date>
                at<lb/> the Synagogue of Congregation<lb/> Sherith-Israel.</p>
            <p>From the different reports, that<lb/> were handed in by the proper of-<lb/>-ficers,
                it has shown that the society<lb/> has succeeded so far, since its</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>short existence in accomplishing<lb/> much good. The many recent<lb/> calls on them
                for charity, has exhausted<lb/> their Treasury. By means of<lb/> a proposed Dramatic
                Performance<lb/> by our Jewish children for their<lb/> Benefit, the society hopes
                soon<lb/> again to meet the many wants<lb/> of the afflicted and destitute.<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. Lichtenstein</persName> has been elected<lb/> Vice-President in lieu
                of <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Rebecca Roggenburger</persName>, who has<lb/> tendered her
                resignation;<lb/> also an election for two more<lb/> matrons was held, which
                resulted<lb/> in the choice of <persName>Mrs. Benjamin</persName><lb/> and
                    <persName>Mrs. Zarinsky</persName>.</p>
            <p>Since my last one of the most<lb/> sad &amp; fatal calamity has befallen to<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. S. Ottenheimer</persName> &amp; her child &amp;<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. S. H. Ulmer</persName> &amp; her child;<lb/> both of the Husbands
                reside in this<lb/> city, &amp; <del>are</del> have not very long been<lb/> married.
                The funeral was very<lb/>
                <sic>solem</sic> and imposing; at least<lb/> 250 persons followed the remains<lb/>
                to their resting place. <persName>Dr. Julius<lb/> Eckman</persName> delivered at the
                cemetery</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>an elaborate and very appropriate<lb/> discourse. I have written out an<lb/>
                obituary, which will explain the<lb/> circumstances of the disaster in<lb/> detail.
                I should be thankful to<lb/> you for <del>the O</del> a place in the<lb/> Occident
                for this obituary, &amp; hope<lb/> you will comply with my desire<lb/> provided the
                style of the writing<lb/> is fit for publication.</p>
            <p>I regret, that I cannot come<lb/> up to my promise in sending you<lb/> some money
                with this mail.<lb/> The principal reason of this is, the<lb/> collector to whom I
                have given<lb/> your accounts, has not been able<lb/> to attend to the same
                right<lb/> yet. I have now $17 on Hand;<lb/> I shall endeavor to sell some
                Books,<lb/> which in connection with some collection<lb/> for the Occident may
                enable me<lb/> to send you some money with<lb/> the mail of the <date>5<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> of March</date>, &amp;<lb/> send accompanying statement
                &amp;c.<lb/> Hoping this may meet you in the<lb/> best of Health I Remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Cauffman H. Meyer</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Turn over</hi>
            </p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p><persName>Mr Roggenburger</persName> &amp; family and<lb/> my brothers, <persName>Mr
                    Greenebaum</persName> &amp;<lb/>
                <persName>Kohland<add>?</add></persName> send their kind regards<lb/> to you
                    <persName role="author">CHM</persName></p>
        </body>
